description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting 12 month fixed term/ secondment opportunity has become available to appoint 3 enthusiastic, dynamic &amp; innovative individuals to our experienced Infection Prevention &amp; Control Team at Lancashire and South Cumbria NHS Foundation Trust as health care assistants. This post is new to the team and is there to support the team with IPC workload related to both Covid 19 and business as usual.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to support the team with auditing compliance against PPE/Hand hygiene and IPC in the environment. The successful candidates will be supporting the training of clinical teams with Fit testing for FFP3 masks and may also be required to undertake swabbing for Covid 19.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A positive approach &amp; the abilty to motivate others, be flexible &amp; have the skills to prioritise your workload are all essential requirements of the post. The work is challenging and no two days are the same. You will be required to work to high standards maintaining a high quality finish to aspects of your work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For any further information or to arrange an informal visit please contact;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sam Ryder, Matron for Infection Prevention &amp; Control on 01254 283605 or 07940470596.&lt;/p&gt;
